description: Located in Gok-dong, Seocho-gu, Seoul, and at the foot of Daemu Mountain, Xianin Mausoleum is the collective name of the two mausoleums of Xianling Mausoleum and Inling Mausoleum. Heonneung is the mausoleum of King Taejong (1367-1422) and Queen Wonkyung (1365-1420), the third king of Joseon Dynasty, and Inneung is the tomb of King Sunjo (1790-1834) and Queen Chunwon (1789-1789), the 24th king of Joseon Dynasty. 1857) of the mausoleum. The tombs of Joseon kings have extremely important historical value and are all included in the UNESCO World Cultural Heritage List.

address: 100 Bucheon-ro 354beon-gil, 원미구 Bucheon-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea

description: Jangchung Gymnasium was built in 1963 and is a gymnasium left over from the Seoul Olympics. The appearance of the gymnasium is very traditional, it is a circular dome-style building. It looks a bit old because of its age.

address: 217-60 Kintex-ro, Ilsanseo-gu, Goyang-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea2600, Dahua-dong, Ilsan-gu, Goyang-si, Gyeonggi-do
